   176(defun make-case-expander ()
   177  "Create a macro expander for CASE.
   178   (case keyform (key form...) ... [(otherwise|t form...)])
   179   Expands to a let binding the keyform, then nested if/eql tests."
   180  (lambda (form)
   181    (let ((keyform (second form))
   182          (clauses (cddr form))
   183          (key-var (gensym "KEY-")))
   184      (labels ((otherwise-clause-p (clause)
   185                 (let ((keys (first clause)))
   186                   (or (eq keys 'otherwise)
   187                       (eq keys 't))))
   188               (make-key-test (key-var key)
   189                 (list 'eql key-var (list 'quote key)))
   190               (make-clause-test (key-var keys)
   191                 (cond
   192                   ;; Single key (not a list)
   193                   ((not (listp keys))
   194                    (make-key-test key-var keys))
   195                   ;; Multiple keys in a list
   196                   ((null (rest keys))
   197                    (make-key-test key-var (first keys)))
   198                   (t
   199                    (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (k)
   200                                        (make-key-test key-var k))
   201                                      keys)))))
   202               (expand-clauses (clauses)
   203                 (if (null clauses)
   204                     nil
   205                     (let* ((clause (first clauses))
   206                            (keys (first clause))
   207                            (body (rest clause)))
   208                       (if (otherwise-clause-p clause)
   209                           ;; otherwise/t clause - just the body
   210                           (cons 'progn body)
   211                           ;; Normal clause
   212                           (list 'if
   213                                 (make-clause-test key-var keys)
   214                                 (cons 'progn body)
   215                                 (expand-clauses (rest clauses))))))))
   216        (list 'let (list (list key-var keyform))
   217              (expand-clauses clauses))))))

   324(defun make-setf-expander ()
   325  "Create a macro expander for SETF.
   326   (setf place value) - Set place to value and return value.
   327   (setf place1 value1 place2 value2 ...) - Multiple pairs."
   328  (lambda (form)
   329    (let ((pairs (rest form)))
   330      (cond
   331        ;; No arguments - return nil
   332        ((null pairs) nil)
   333        ;; Odd number of arguments - error
   334        ((oddp (length pairs))
   335         (error 'clysm/lib/setf-expanders:odd-argument-count
   336                :macro-name 'setf
   337                :argument-count (length pairs)))
   338        ;; Single pair
   339        ((= 2 (length pairs))
   340         (expand-single-setf (first pairs) (second pairs)))
   341        ;; Multiple pairs - expand to progn of single setf forms
   342        (t
   343         (cons 'progn
   344               (loop for (place value) on pairs by #'cddr
   345                     collect (list 'setf place value))))))))

   347(defun expand-single-setf (place value)
   348  "Expand a single (setf place value) form."
   349  (cond
   350    ;; Simple variable case
   351    ((and (symbolp place)
   352          (not (keywordp place))
   353          (not (eq place t))
   354          (not (eq place nil)))
   355     (list 'setq place value))
   356    ;; Compound place - use setf expansion protocol
   357    ((consp place)
   358     (multiple-value-bind (temps vals stores store-form access-form)
   359         (clysm/lib/setf-expanders:get-setf-expansion* place)
   360       (declare (ignore access-form))
   361       (let ((store (first stores))
   362             (bindings (mapcar #'list temps vals)))
   363         ;; Build the expansion:
   364         ;; (let ((temp1 val1) (temp2 val2) ...)
   365         ;;   (let ((store value))
   366         ;;     store-form))
   367         (if bindings
   368             (list 'let bindings
   369                   (list 'let (list (list store value))
   370                         store-form))
   371             ;; No temps needed
   372             (list 'let (list (list store value))
   373                   store-form)))))
   374    ;; Invalid place (constant)
   375    ((or (keywordp place) (eq place t) (eq place nil))
   376     (error 'clysm/lib/setf-expanders:constant-modification-error
   377            :place place))
   378    ;; Invalid place (other)
   379    (t
   380     (error 'clysm/lib/setf-expanders:invalid-place
   381            :place place))))

   387  (lambda (form)
   388    (let ((pairs (rest form)))
   389      (cond
   390        ;; No arguments - return nil
   391        ((null pairs) nil)
   392        ;; Odd number of arguments - error
   393        ((oddp (length pairs))
   394         (error "PSETQ requires an even number of arguments"))
   395        ;; Single pair - expand to setq
   396        ((= (length pairs) 2)
   397         (list 'setq (first pairs) (second pairs)))
   398        ;; Multiple pairs - expand to parallel assignment
   399        (t
   400         (let ((temps nil)
   401               (bindings nil)
   402               (setqs nil))
   403           ;; Collect all the information
   404           (loop for (var value) on pairs by #'cddr
   405                 do (let ((temp (gensym "PSETQ-")))
   406                      (push temp temps)
   407                      (push (list temp value) bindings)
   408                      (push var setqs)
   409                      (push temp setqs)))
   410           ;; Build: (let ((temp1 val1) ...) (setq var1 temp1 ...) nil)
   411           (list 'let (nreverse bindings)

   419    (let ((pairs (rest form)))
   420      (cond
   421        ;; No arguments - return nil
   422        ((null pairs) nil)
   423        ;; Odd number of arguments - error
   424        ((oddp (length pairs))
   425         (error 'clysm/lib/setf-expanders:odd-argument-count
   426                :macro-name 'psetf
   427                :argument-count (length pairs)))
   428        ;; Expand to parallel assignment
   429        (t
   430         (let ((temps nil)
   431               (bindings nil)
   432               (setfs nil))
   433           ;; Collect all the information
   434           (loop for (place value) on pairs by #'cddr
   435                 do (let ((temp (gensym "PSETF-")))
   436                      (push temp temps)
   437                      (push (list temp value) bindings)
   438                      (push (list 'setf place temp) setfs)))
   439           ;; Build: (let ((temp1 val1) (temp2 val2) ...) (setf place1 temp1) ... nil)
   440           (list* 'let (nreverse bindings)
   441                  (append (nreverse setfs) (list nil)))))))))

   500(defun make-rotatef-expander ()
   501  "Create a macro expander for ROTATEF.
   502   (rotatef place1 place2 ...) - Rotate values cyclically."
   503  (lambda (form)
   504    (let ((places (rest form)))
   505      (cond
   506        ;; No places - return nil
   507        ((null places) nil)
   508        ;; Single place - no-op, return nil
   509        ((null (rest places)) nil)
   510        ;; Two places - swap
   511        ((= 2 (length places))
   512         (let ((temp (gensym "ROTATE-")))
   513           (list 'let (list (list temp (first places)))
   514                 (list 'setf (first places) (second places))
   515                 (list 'setf (second places) temp)
   516                 nil)))
   517        ;; Multiple places - rotate
   518        (t
   519         ;; Save all values in temps, then assign rotated
   520         (let ((temps (loop for p in places collect (gensym "ROTATE-"))))
   521           (list* 'let (mapcar #'list temps places)
   522                  (append
   523                   ;; Assign rotated values
   524                   (loop for place in places
   525                         for i from 0
   526                         for temp = (nth (mod (1+ i) (length temps)) temps)
   527                         collect (list 'setf place temp))
   528                   (list nil)))))))))

   530(defun make-shiftf-expander ()
   531  "Create a macro expander for SHIFTF.
   532   (shiftf place1 place2 ... newvalue) - Shift values left, return first."
   533  (lambda (form)
   534    (let ((args (rest form)))
   535      (cond
   536        ;; Need at least 2 arguments (place + newvalue)
   537        ((< (length args) 2)
   538         (error "SHIFTF requires at least a place and a new value"))
   539        ;; Single place + newvalue
   540        ((= 2 (length args))
   541         (let ((place (first args))
   542               (newvalue (second args))
   543               (result-var (gensym "SHIFTF-")))
   544           ;; (prog1 place (setf place newvalue))
   545           (list 'let (list (list result-var place))
   546                 (list 'setf place newvalue)
   547                 result-var)))
   548        ;; Multiple places + newvalue
   549        (t
   550         (let* ((places (butlast args))
   551                (newvalue (car (last args)))
   552                (temps (loop for p in places collect (gensym "SHIFTF-")))
   553                (result-var (first temps)))
   554           ;; Save all values, then shift
   555           (list* 'let (mapcar #'list temps places)
   556                  (append
   557                   ;; Assign shifted values (place[i] = temp[i+1])
   558                   (loop for place in (butlast places)
   559                         for temp in (rest temps)
   560                         collect (list 'setf place temp))
   561                   ;; Last place gets newvalue
   562                   (list (list 'setf (car (last places)) newvalue))
   563                   ;; Return first saved value
   564                   (list result-var)))))))))

   707(defun parse-loop-clauses (clauses ctx)
   708  "Parse LOOP clauses into structured clause objects in CTX.
   709   CLAUSES is a list of forms from (loop ...).
   710   Returns the remaining unparsed clauses (should be nil on success)."
   711  (loop while clauses do
   712    (let ((keyword (first clauses)))
   713      (cond
   714        ;; Named clause
   715        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'named)
   716         (setf (loop-context-name ctx) (second clauses))
   717         (setf clauses (cddr clauses)))
   718
   719        ;; FOR/AS iteration clauses
   720        ((or (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'for)
   721             (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'as))
   722         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   723             (parse-for-clause (rest clauses) ctx)
   724           (push clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
   725           (setf clauses rest)))
   726
   727        ;; WITH variable binding
   728        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'with)
   729         (multiple-value-bind (bindings rest)
   730             (parse-with-clause (rest clauses) ctx)
   731           (setf (loop-context-with-bindings ctx)
   732                 (append (loop-context-with-bindings ctx) bindings))
   733           (setf clauses rest)))
   734
   735        ;; Accumulation clauses
   736        ((member keyword '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
   737                           maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
   738                           append appending nconc nconcing)
   739                 :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   740         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   741             (parse-accumulation-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   742           (push clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
   743           (setf clauses rest)))
   744
   745        ;; Termination clauses
   746        ((member keyword '(while until) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   747         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   748             (parse-termination-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   749           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   750           (setf clauses rest)))
   751
   752        ;; Boolean aggregation clauses
   753        ((member keyword '(always never thereis) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   754         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   755             (parse-boolean-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   756           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   757           (setf clauses rest)))
   758
   759        ;; RETURN clause
   760        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'return)
   761         (let ((clause (make-loop-termination-clause
   762                        :type :return
   763                        :expr (second clauses))))
   764           (push clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
   765           (setf clauses (cddr clauses))))
   766
   767        ;; Conditional clauses
   768        ((member keyword '(if when unless) :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   769         (multiple-value-bind (clause rest)
   770             (parse-conditional-clause keyword (rest clauses) ctx)
   771           (push clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
   772           (setf clauses rest)))
   773
   774        ;; DO/DOING clause
   775        ((or (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'do)
   776             (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'doing))
   777         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   778             (parse-do-forms (rest clauses))
   779           (dolist (form forms)
   780             (push form (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)))
   781           (setf clauses rest)))
   782
   783        ;; INITIALLY clause
   784        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'initially)
   785         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   786             (parse-compound-forms (rest clauses))
   787           (setf (loop-context-initially-forms ctx)
   788                 (append (loop-context-initially-forms ctx) forms))
   789           (setf clauses rest)))
   790
   791        ;; FINALLY clause
   792        ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'finally)
   793         (multiple-value-bind (forms rest)
   794             (parse-compound-forms (rest clauses))
   795           (setf (loop-context-finally-forms ctx)
   796                 (append (loop-context-finally-forms ctx) forms))
   797           (setf clauses rest)))
   798
   799        ;; Unknown - might be a form for simple loop
   800        (t
   801         ;; For simple loop, treat remaining as body
   802         (push keyword (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
   803         (setf clauses (rest clauses))))))
   804  ;; Reverse collected lists to maintain order
   805  (setf (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx)
   806        (nreverse (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx)))
   807  (setf (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx)
   808        (nreverse (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx)))
   809  (setf (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx)
   810        (nreverse (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx)))
   811  (setf (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)
   812        (nreverse (loop-context-body-clauses ctx)))
   813  ctx)

   824(defun parse-for-clause (clauses ctx)
   825  "Parse a FOR/AS clause. Returns (values clause remaining-clauses)."
   826  (declare (ignore ctx))
   827  (let ((var (first clauses))
   828        (rest (rest clauses)))
   829    ;; Determine the type of FOR clause
   830    (cond
   831      ;; FOR var FROM ... (arithmetic)
   832      ((member (first rest) '(from upfrom downfrom to below above downto by)
   833               :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
   834       (parse-for-arithmetic var rest))
   835      ;; FOR var IN list
   836      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'in)
   837       (parse-for-in var rest))
   838      ;; FOR var ON list
   839      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'on)
   840       (parse-for-on var rest))
   841      ;; FOR var ACROSS vector
   842      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'across)
   843       (parse-for-across var rest))
   844      ;; FOR var = expr [THEN step-expr]
   845      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) '=)
   846       (parse-for-equals var rest))
   847      ;; FOR var BEING THE HASH-KEYS/HASH-VALUES OF hash-table
   848      ((loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'being)
   849       (parse-for-hash var rest))
   850      ;; Default: treat as = with no THEN
   851      (t
   852       (values (make-loop-iter-equals
   853                :var var
   854                :clause-type :equals
   855                :init-form nil
   856                :then-form nil)
   857               rest)))))

   982               :hash-form hash-form
   983               :mode mode)
   984              final-rest))))

   986(defun parse-with-clause (clauses ctx)
   987  "Parse WITH var [= expr] [AND var2 [= expr2] ...]. Returns (values bindings rest)."
   988  (declare (ignore ctx))
   989  (let ((bindings nil)
   990        (rest clauses))
   991    (loop
   992      (let ((var (first rest)))
   993        (setf rest (rest rest))
   994        (if (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) '=)
   995            (progn
   996              (push (list var (second rest)) bindings)
   997              (setf rest (cddr rest)))
   998            (push (list var nil) bindings))
   999        ;; Check for AND - if present, skip it and continue parsing
  1000        (if (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'and)
  1001            (setf rest (rest rest))  ; consume AND keyword
  1002            (return))))  ; no AND, done with WITH clause
  1003    (values (nreverse bindings) rest)))

  1005(defun parse-accumulation-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
  1006  "Parse COLLECT/SUM/COUNT/etc accumulation clause."
  1007  (declare (ignore ctx))
  1008  (let* ((type (intern (string-upcase
  1009                        (string-right-trim "ING"
  1010                                           (symbol-name keyword)))
  1011                       :keyword))
  1012         (expr (first clauses))
  1013         (rest (rest clauses))
  1014         (into-var nil))
  1015    ;; Check for INTO
  1016    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'into)
  1017      (setf into-var (second rest))
  1018      (setf rest (cddr rest)))
  1019    (values (make-loop-accumulation-clause
  1020             :type type
  1021             :expr expr
  1022             :into-var into-var
  1023             :acc-var (or into-var (gensym "LOOP-ACC-")))
  1024            rest)))

  1026(defun parse-termination-clause (keyword clauses ctx)

  1029  (let ((type (if (loop-keyword-eq keyword 'while) :while :until))
  1030        (expr (first clauses)))
  1031    (values (make-loop-termination-clause
  1032             :type type
  1033             :expr expr)
  1034            (rest clauses))))

  1036(defun parse-boolean-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
  1037  "Parse ALWAYS/NEVER/THEREIS boolean aggregation clause."
  1038  (declare (ignore ctx))
  1039  (let ((type (cond
  1040                ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'always) :always)
  1041                ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'never) :never)
  1042                (t :thereis)))
  1043        (expr (first clauses)))
  1044    (values (make-loop-termination-clause
  1045             :type type
  1046             :expr expr)
  1047            (rest clauses))))

  1049(defun parse-conditional-clause (keyword clauses ctx)
  1050  "Parse IF/WHEN/UNLESS conditional clause."
  1051  (declare (ignore ctx))
  1052  (let* ((type (cond
  1053                 ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'if) :if)
  1054                 ((loop-keyword-eq keyword 'when) :when)
  1055                 (t :unless)))
  1056         (condition (first clauses))
  1057         (rest (rest clauses))
  1058         (then-clauses nil)
  1059         (else-clauses nil))
  1060    ;; Parse then-clauses until ELSE/END or another major keyword
  1061    (multiple-value-bind (forms remaining)
  1062        (parse-conditional-body rest)
  1063      (setf then-clauses forms)
  1064      (setf rest remaining))
  1065    ;; Check for ELSE
  1066    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'else)
  1067      (multiple-value-bind (forms remaining)
  1068          (parse-conditional-body (rest rest))
  1069        (setf else-clauses forms)
  1070        (setf rest remaining)))
  1071    ;; Check for END
  1072    (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'end)
  1073      (setf rest (rest rest)))
  1074    (values (make-loop-conditional-clause
  1075             :type type
  1076             :condition condition
  1077             :then-clauses then-clauses
  1078             :else-clauses else-clauses)
  1079            rest)))

  1081(defun parse-conditional-body (clauses)
  1082  "Parse forms in a conditional body until ELSE/END/major keyword.
  1083   Handles DO/DOING prefix and accumulation keywords as ANSI CL requires."
  1084  (let ((forms nil)
  1085        (rest clauses))
  1086    ;; Check for optional DO/DOING prefix (valid inside conditionals)
  1087    (when (and rest
  1088               (symbolp (first rest))
  1089               (or (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'do)
  1090                   (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'doing)))
  1091      (setf rest (rest rest)))  ; skip DO/DOING
  1092    (loop while rest do
  1093      (let ((form (first rest)))
  1094        ;; Stop at ELSE, END, or major clause keywords
  1095        (when (and (symbolp form)
  1096                   (or (loop-keyword-eq form 'else)
  1097                       (loop-keyword-eq form 'end)
  1098                       (member form '(for as with while until
  1099                                      always never thereis return
  1100                                      initially finally
  1101                                      if when unless named)
  1102                               :test #'loop-keyword-eq)))
  1103          (return))
  1104        ;; Handle AND chaining - may have optional DO/DOING after AND
  1105        (when (loop-keyword-eq form 'and)
  1106          (setf rest (rest rest))
  1107          ;; Skip optional DO/DOING after AND
  1108          (when (and rest
  1109                     (symbolp (first rest))
  1110                     (or (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'do)
  1111                         (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'doing)))
  1112            (setf rest (rest rest)))
  1113          (setf form (first rest)))
  1114        ;; Handle accumulation keywords specially - they consume an expression
  1115        (cond
  1116          ((member form '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1117                          maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1118                          append appending nconc nconcing)
  1119                   :test #'loop-keyword-eq)
  1120           ;; Accumulation: form + expr = two tokens
  1121           (let ((acc-keyword form)
  1122                 (acc-expr (second rest)))
  1123             ;; Check for INTO
  1124             (setf rest (cddr rest))
  1125             (when (loop-keyword-eq (first rest) 'into)
  1126               (setf rest (cddr rest)))  ; skip INTO and var
  1127             (push (list acc-keyword acc-expr) forms)))
  1128          (t
  1129           (push form forms)
  1130           (setf rest (rest rest))))))
  1131    (values (nreverse forms) rest)))
  1132
  1133(defun parse-do-forms (clauses)
  1134  "Parse forms after DO/DOING until next keyword."
  1135  (let ((forms nil)
  1136        (rest clauses))
  1137    (loop while rest do
  1138      (let ((form (first rest)))
  1139        (when (and (symbolp form) (loop-keyword-p form))
  1140          (return))
  1141        (push form forms)
  1142        (setf rest (rest rest))))
  1143    (values (nreverse forms) rest)))
  1144
  1145(defun parse-compound-forms (clauses)
  1146  "Parse compound forms (for INITIALLY/FINALLY)."
  1147  (parse-do-forms clauses))

  1153(defun expand-loop (ctx)
  1154  "Expand parsed LOOP context to tagbody-based code."
  1155  (let* ((block-name (or (loop-context-name ctx) nil))
  1156         (loop-start (gensym "LOOP-START-"))
  1157         (loop-end (gensym "LOOP-END-"))
  1158         ;; Generate variable bindings
  1159         (iter-bindings (generate-iteration-bindings ctx))
  1160         (acc-bindings (generate-accumulator-bindings ctx))
  1161         (with-bindings (loop-context-with-bindings ctx))
  1162         (all-bindings (append iter-bindings acc-bindings with-bindings))
  1163         ;; Generate code sections
  1164         (termination-tests (generate-termination-tests ctx loop-end))
  1165         (body-code (generate-body-code ctx))
  1166         (acc-updates (generate-accumulator-updates ctx))
  1167         (step-code (generate-iteration-steps ctx))
  1168         (result-form (generate-result-form ctx)))
  1169    ;; Build the expansion
  1170    ;; Feature 043: Use LET* for sequential bindings (FOR vars may depend on earlier WITH vars)
  1171    `(let* ,all-bindings
  1172       (block ,block-name
  1173         (tagbody
  1174            ,@(loop-context-initially-forms ctx)
  1175            ,loop-start
  1176            ,@termination-tests
  1177            ,@body-code
  1178            ,@acc-updates
  1179            ,@step-code
  1180            (go ,loop-start)
  1181            ,loop-end)
  1182         ,@(loop-context-finally-forms ctx)
  1183         ,result-form))))

  1189(defun generate-iteration-bindings (ctx)
  1190  "Generate bindings for iteration variables."
  1191  (let ((bindings nil))
  1192    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1193      (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause)))
  1194        (cond
  1195          ;; Arithmetic iteration
  1196          ((loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1197           (let ((init (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-from clause)
  1198                           (loop-iter-arithmetic-upfrom clause)
  1199                           (loop-iter-arithmetic-downfrom clause)
  1200                           0)))
  1201             (push (list var init) bindings)))
  1202          ;; IN list iteration
  1203          ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1204           (let ((list-form (loop-iter-in-list-form clause))
  1205                 (list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause)))
  1206             (push (list list-var list-form) bindings)
  1207             (push (list var `(car ,list-var)) bindings)))
  1208          ;; ON list iteration
  1209          ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1210           (let ((list-form (loop-iter-on-list-form clause))
  1211                 (list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause)))
  1212             (push (list list-var list-form) bindings)
  1213             (push (list var list-var) bindings)))
  1214          ;; ACROSS vector iteration
  1215          ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1216           (let ((vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause))
  1217                 (idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause)))
  1218             (push (list vec-var (loop-iter-across-vector-form clause)) bindings)
  1219             (push (list idx-var 0) bindings)
  1220             (push (list var `(aref ,vec-var ,idx-var)) bindings)))
  1221          ;; = THEN iteration
  1222          ((loop-iter-equals-p clause)
  1223           (push (list var (loop-iter-equals-init-form clause)) bindings)))))
  1224    (nreverse bindings)))

  1226(defun extract-conditional-accum-types (clause)
  1227  "Extract accumulation types from a conditional clause's body."
  1228  (let ((types nil))
  1229    (labels ((check-form (form)
  1230               (when (and (listp form) (= 2 (length form))
  1231                          (member (first form)
  1232                                  '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1233                                    maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1234                                    append appending nconc nconcing)
  1235                                  :test #'loop-keyword-eq))
  1236                 (push (intern (string-upcase
  1237                                (string-right-trim "ING" (symbol-name (first form))))
  1238                               :keyword)
  1239                       types))))
  1240      (mapc #'check-form (loop-conditional-clause-then-clauses clause))
  1241      (mapc #'check-form (loop-conditional-clause-else-clauses clause)))
  1242    types))

  1244(defun generate-accumulator-bindings (ctx)
  1245  "Generate bindings for accumulator variables.
  1246   Handles both top-level and conditional accumulations."
  1247  (let ((bindings nil)
  1248        (seen-types (make-hash-table :test 'eq))
  1249        (type-to-var (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1250    ;; First collect all accumulation types including from conditionals
  1251    (dolist (clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1252      (let ((type (loop-accumulation-clause-type clause))
  1253            (acc-var (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var clause)))
  1254        (unless (gethash type seen-types)
  1255          (setf (gethash type seen-types) t)
  1256          (setf (gethash type type-to-var) acc-var))))
  1257    ;; Also scan body clauses for conditional accumulations
  1258    (dolist (clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
  1259      (when (loop-conditional-clause-p clause)
  1260        (dolist (type (extract-conditional-accum-types clause))
  1261          (unless (gethash type seen-types)
  1262            (setf (gethash type seen-types) t)
  1263            (setf (gethash type type-to-var) (gensym "LOOP-ACC-"))))))
  1264    ;; Store the type-to-var map in context for later use
  1265    (setf (loop-context-result-form ctx) type-to-var)
  1266    ;; Generate bindings for all seen accumulation types
  1267    (maphash (lambda (type acc-var)
  1268               (let ((init (case type
  1269                             ((:collect :append :nconc) 'nil)
  1270                             ((:sum :count) 0)
  1271                             ((:maximize :minimize) 'nil))))
  1272                 (push (list acc-var init) bindings)
  1273                 ;; For COLLECT, add tail pointer for efficiency
  1274                 (when (eq type :collect)
  1275                   (let ((tail-var (gensym "LOOP-TAIL-")))
  1276                     (push (list tail-var 'nil) bindings)))))
  1277             type-to-var)
  1278    (nreverse bindings)))

  1280(defun generate-termination-tests (ctx loop-end)
  1281  "Generate termination test code."
  1282  (let ((tests nil))
  1283    ;; Add iteration exhaustion tests
  1284    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1285      (cond
  1286        ;; Arithmetic with TO
  1287        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1288              (loop-iter-arithmetic-to clause))
  1289         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1290               (to (loop-iter-arithmetic-to clause)))
  1291           (push `(if (> ,var ,to) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1292        ;; Arithmetic with BELOW
  1293        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1294              (loop-iter-arithmetic-below clause))
  1295         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1296               (below (loop-iter-arithmetic-below clause)))
  1297           (push `(if (>= ,var ,below) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1298        ;; Arithmetic with DOWNTO
  1299        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1300              (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause))
  1301         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1302               (downto (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause)))
  1303           (push `(if (< ,var ,downto) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1304        ;; Arithmetic with ABOVE
  1305        ((and (loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1306              (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause))
  1307         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1308               (above (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause)))
  1309           (push `(if (<= ,var ,above) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1310        ;; IN list - terminate when list is exhausted
  1311        ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1312         (let ((list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause)))
  1313           (push `(if (null ,list-var) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1314        ;; ON list - terminate when list is exhausted
  1315        ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1316         (let ((list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause)))
  1317           (push `(if (null ,list-var) (go ,loop-end)) tests)))
  1318        ;; ACROSS vector - terminate when index reaches length
  1319        ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1320         (let ((idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause))
  1321               (vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause)))
  1322           (push `(if (>= ,idx-var (length ,vec-var))
  1323                      (go ,loop-end))
  1324                 tests)))))
  1325    ;; Add WHILE/UNTIL termination tests
  1326    (dolist (clause (loop-context-termination-clauses ctx))
  1327      (case (loop-termination-clause-type clause)
  1328        (:while
  1329         (push `(if (not ,(loop-termination-clause-expr clause))
  1330                    (go ,loop-end))
  1331               tests))
  1332        (:until
  1333         (push `(if ,(loop-termination-clause-expr clause)
  1334                    (go ,loop-end))
  1335               tests))))
  1336    (nreverse tests)))

  1338(defun generate-body-code (ctx)
  1339  "Generate body code from DO and conditional clauses."
  1340  (let ((code nil)
  1341        ;; Get the type-to-var map stored during accumulator binding generation
  1342        (acc-var-map (loop-context-result-form ctx)))
  1343    ;; If acc-var-map is a hash table, use it; otherwise create new
  1344    (unless (hash-table-p acc-var-map)
  1345      (setf acc-var-map (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1346    (dolist (clause (loop-context-body-clauses ctx))
  1347      (if (loop-conditional-clause-p clause)
  1348          (push (expand-conditional-clause clause acc-var-map) code)
  1349          (push clause code)))
  1350    (nreverse code)))

  1352(defun expand-conditional-form (form acc-var-map)
  1353  "Expand a single form that may be an accumulation inside a conditional.
  1354   ACC-VAR-MAP maps accumulation types to their accumulator variables."
  1355  (if (and (listp form) (= 2 (length form))
  1356           (member (first form) '(collect collecting sum summing count counting
  1357                                  maximize maximizing minimize minimizing
  1358                                  append appending nconc nconcing)
  1359                   :test #'loop-keyword-eq))
  1360      ;; This is an accumulation form - expand it
  1361      (let* ((keyword (first form))
  1362             (expr (second form))
  1363             (type (intern (string-upcase
  1364                            (string-right-trim "ING" (symbol-name keyword)))
  1365                           :keyword))
  1366             (acc-var (or (gethash type acc-var-map)
  1367                          (gensym "LOOP-ACC-"))))
  1368        ;; Store for later use
  1369        (setf (gethash type acc-var-map) acc-var)
  1370        ;; Return the update form
  1371        (case type
  1372          (:collect `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var (list ,expr))))
  1373          (:sum `(setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1374          (:count `(when ,expr (setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var 1))))
  1375          (:maximize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (max ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1376          (:minimize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (min ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1377          (:append `(setq ,acc-var (append ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1378          (:nconc `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var ,expr)))))
  1379      ;; Not an accumulation - return as-is
  1380      form))

  1382(defun expand-conditional-clause (clause &optional (acc-var-map nil))
  1383  "Expand a conditional clause to IF/WHEN/UNLESS form.
  1384   ACC-VAR-MAP is used to share accumulator variables across clauses."
  1385  (let ((acc-var-map (or acc-var-map (make-hash-table :test 'eq)))
  1386        (type (loop-conditional-clause-type clause))
  1387        (cond-form (loop-conditional-clause-condition clause))
  1388        (then-forms (loop-conditional-clause-then-clauses clause))
  1389        (else-forms (loop-conditional-clause-else-clauses clause)))
  1390    ;; Expand any accumulation forms in then/else clauses
  1391    (let ((expanded-then (mapcar (lambda (f) (expand-conditional-form f acc-var-map))
  1392                                 then-forms))
  1393          (expanded-else (mapcar (lambda (f) (expand-conditional-form f acc-var-map))
  1394                                 else-forms)))
  1395      (case type
  1396        ((:if :when)
  1397         (if expanded-else
  1398             `(if ,cond-form
  1399                  (progn ,@expanded-then)
  1400                  (progn ,@expanded-else))
  1401             `(when ,cond-form ,@expanded-then)))
  1402        (:unless
  1403         (if expanded-else
  1404             `(if (not ,cond-form)
  1405                  (progn ,@expanded-then)
  1406                  (progn ,@expanded-else))
  1407             `(unless ,cond-form ,@expanded-then)))))))

  1409(defun generate-accumulator-updates (ctx)
  1410  "Generate accumulator update code."
  1411  (let ((updates nil))
  1412    (dolist (clause (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1413      (let* ((type (loop-accumulation-clause-type clause))
  1414             (expr (loop-accumulation-clause-expr clause))
  1415             (acc-var (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var clause)))
  1416        (push
  1417         (case type
  1418           (:collect `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var (list ,expr))))
  1419           (:sum `(setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1420           (:count `(when ,expr (setq ,acc-var (+ ,acc-var 1))))
  1421           (:maximize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (max ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1422           (:minimize `(setq ,acc-var (if ,acc-var (min ,acc-var ,expr) ,expr)))
  1423           (:append `(setq ,acc-var (append ,acc-var ,expr)))
  1424           (:nconc `(setq ,acc-var (nconc ,acc-var ,expr))))
  1425         updates)))
  1426    (nreverse updates)))

  1428(defun generate-iteration-steps (ctx)
  1429  "Generate iteration stepping code using psetq for parallel stepping."
  1430  (let ((step-pairs nil))
  1431    (dolist (clause (loop-context-iteration-clauses ctx))
  1432      (cond
  1433        ;; Arithmetic stepping
  1434        ((loop-iter-arithmetic-p clause)
  1435         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1436               (by (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-by clause) 1))
  1437               (descending (or (loop-iter-arithmetic-downto clause)
  1438                               (loop-iter-arithmetic-downfrom clause)
  1439                               (loop-iter-arithmetic-above clause))))
  1440           (push var step-pairs)
  1441           (push (if descending
  1442                     `(- ,var ,by)
  1443                     `(+ ,var ,by))
  1444                 step-pairs)))
  1445        ;; IN list stepping - step the list-var, then update var
  1446        ((loop-iter-in-p clause)
  1447         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1448               (list-var (loop-iter-in-list-var clause))
  1449               (step-fn (or (loop-iter-in-step-fn clause) 'cdr)))
  1450           ;; Step the list variable
  1451           (push list-var step-pairs)
  1452           (push `(,step-fn ,list-var) step-pairs)
  1453           ;; Update the loop variable to the new car
  1454           (push var step-pairs)
  1455           (push `(car ,list-var) step-pairs)))
  1456        ;; ON list stepping - step the list-var, var is the same
  1457        ((loop-iter-on-p clause)
  1458         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1459               (list-var (loop-iter-on-list-var clause))
  1460               (step-fn (or (loop-iter-on-step-fn clause) 'cdr)))
  1461           ;; Step the list variable
  1462           (push list-var step-pairs)
  1463           (push `(,step-fn ,list-var) step-pairs)
  1464           ;; Update the loop variable (which is the same as list-var content)
  1465           (push var step-pairs)
  1466           (push list-var step-pairs)))
  1467        ;; ACROSS vector stepping
  1468        ((loop-iter-across-p clause)
  1469         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause))
  1470               (idx-var (loop-iter-across-index-var clause))
  1471               (vec-var (loop-iter-across-vec-var clause)))
  1472           ;; Increment the index
  1473           (push idx-var step-pairs)
  1474           (push `(+ ,idx-var 1) step-pairs)
  1475           ;; Update the loop variable
  1476           (push var step-pairs)
  1477           (push `(aref ,vec-var ,idx-var) step-pairs)))
  1478        ;; = THEN stepping
  1479        ((and (loop-iter-equals-p clause)
  1480              (loop-iter-equals-then-form clause))
  1481         (let ((var (loop-iteration-clause-var clause)))
  1482           (push var step-pairs)
  1483           (push (loop-iter-equals-then-form clause) step-pairs)))))
  1484    (when step-pairs
  1485      (list (cons 'psetq (nreverse step-pairs))))))
  1486
  1487(defun generate-result-form (ctx)
  1488  "Generate the result form for the LOOP.
  1489   Handles both top-level and conditional accumulations."
  1490  (let ((accumulators (loop-context-accumulation-clauses ctx))
  1491        (type-to-var (loop-context-result-form ctx)))
  1492    (cond
  1493      ;; Has top-level accumulators - use first one
  1494      (accumulators
  1495       (loop-accumulation-clause-acc-var (first accumulators)))
  1496      ;; Check for conditional accumulations in type-to-var map
  1497      ((and (hash-table-p type-to-var) (> (hash-table-count type-to-var) 0))
  1498       ;; Return the first accumulator found
  1499       (block find-acc
  1500         (maphash (lambda (type acc-var)
  1501                    (declare (ignore type))
  1502                    (return-from find-acc acc-var))
  1503                  type-to-var)
  1504         'nil))
  1505      ;; No accumulation -> return NIL
  1506      (t 'nil))))

  1512(defun make-loop-expander ()
  1513  "Create a macro expander for LOOP."
  1514  (lambda (form)
  1515    (let* ((clauses (rest form))
  1516           (ctx (make-loop-context)))
  1517      ;; Handle simple infinite loop: (loop body...)
  1518      (if (and clauses
  1519               (not (symbolp (first clauses))))
  1520          ;; Simple loop - just wrap in infinite loop
  1521          `(block nil
  1522             (tagbody
  1523                loop-start
  1524                ,@clauses
  1525                (go loop-start)))
  1526          ;; Extended loop - parse and expand
  1527          (progn
  1528            (parse-loop-clauses clauses ctx)
  1529            (expand-loop ctx))))))

  1539(defun type-specifier-to-predicate (typespec value-sym)
  1540  "Convert a type specifier to a predicate form.
  1541   TYPESPEC: Type specifier (symbol or list)
  1542   VALUE-SYM: Symbol to test
  1543   Returns: Form that evaluates to T or NIL
  1544
  1545   Examples:
  1546     (type-specifier-to-predicate 'integer 'x) => (integerp x)
  1547     (type-specifier-to-predicate '(or integer symbol) 'x)
  1548       => (or (integerp x) (symbolp x))"
  1549  (cond
  1550    ;; Atomic type specifiers
  1551    ((eq typespec 'integer) (list 'integerp value-sym))
  1552    ((eq typespec 'fixnum) (list 'integerp value-sym))  ; fixnum = integer in Clysm
  1553    ((eq typespec 'symbol) (list 'symbolp value-sym))
  1554    ((eq typespec 'cons) (list 'consp value-sym))
  1555    ((eq typespec 'null) (list 'null value-sym))
  1556    ((eq typespec 'list) (list 'listp value-sym))
  1557    ((eq typespec 'number) (list 'numberp value-sym))
  1558    ((eq typespec 'float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1559    ((eq typespec 'single-float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1560    ((eq typespec 'double-float) (list 'floatp value-sym))
  1561    ((eq typespec 'ratio) (list 'ratiop value-sym))
  1562    ((eq typespec 'rational) (list 'rationalp value-sym))
  1563    ((eq typespec 'real) (list 'realp value-sym))
  1564    ((eq typespec 'character) (list 'characterp value-sym))
  1565    ((eq typespec 'function) (list 'functionp value-sym))
  1566    ((eq typespec 'string) (list 'stringp value-sym))
  1567    ((eq typespec 'vector) (list 'vectorp value-sym))
  1568    ((eq typespec 'array) (list 'arrayp value-sym))
  1569    ((eq typespec 'hash-table) (list 'hash-table-p value-sym))
  1570    ((eq typespec 'package) (list 'packagep value-sym))
  1571    ((eq typespec 'stream) (list 'streamp value-sym))
  1572    ((eq typespec 'keyword) (list 'keywordp value-sym))
  1573    ((eq typespec 'atom) (list 'atom value-sym))
  1574    ((eq typespec 't) t)
  1575    ;; Compound type specifiers
  1576    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'or))
  1577     (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts) (type-specifier-to-predicate ts value-sym))
  1578                       (cdr typespec))))
  1579    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'and))
  1580     (cons 'and (mapcar (lambda (ts) (type-specifier-to-predicate ts value-sym))
  1581                        (cdr typespec))))
  1582    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'not))
  1583     (list 'not (type-specifier-to-predicate (cadr typespec) value-sym)))
  1584    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'member))
  1585     (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (item) (list 'eql value-sym (list 'quote item)))
  1586                       (cdr typespec))))
  1587    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'satisfies))
  1588     (list 'funcall (list 'function (cadr typespec)) value-sym))
  1589    ((and (listp typespec) (eq (car typespec) 'eql))
  1590     (list 'eql value-sym (list 'quote (cadr typespec))))
  1591    ;; Unknown type - fall back to typep
  1592    (t (list 'typep value-sym (list 'quote typespec)))))
  1593

  1598(defun construct-expected-type (clauses)
  1599  "Construct expected-type from typecase clauses for type-error.
  1600   CLAUSES: List of (type-specifier . body-forms)
  1601   Returns: Type specifier (or type1 type2 ...)
  1602
  1603   Example:
  1604     (construct-expected-type '((integer ...) (symbol ...) (cons ...)))
  1605       => (or integer symbol cons)"
  1606  (let ((types nil))
  1607    (dolist (clause clauses)
  1608      (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1609        (cond
  1610          ;; Multiple types in a list: ((type1 type2) body...)
  1611          ((and (listp type-spec) (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1612           (dolist (ts type-spec)
  1613             (push ts types)))
  1614          ;; Single type
  1615          (t
  1616           (push type-spec types)))))
  1617    (setf types (nreverse types))
  1618    (if (= 1 (length types))
  1619        (first types)
  1620        (cons 'or types))))

  1626(defun validate-exhaustive-clauses (clauses macro-name)
  1627  "Validate that clauses do not contain otherwise/t (for etypecase/ctypecase).
  1628   CLAUSES: List of clause forms
  1629   MACRO-NAME: Symbol for error message (etypecase or ctypecase)
  1630   Signals: error if otherwise or t clause found"
  1631  (dolist (clause clauses)
  1632    (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1633      (when (or (eq type-spec 'otherwise)
  1634                (eq type-spec 't))
  1635        (error "~A: ~A clause not allowed in ~A"
  1636               macro-name type-spec macro-name)))))

  1646(defun make-typecase-expander ()
  1647  "Create a macro expander for TYPECASE.
  1648   (typecase keyform (type form...) ... [(otherwise|t form...)])
  1649   Expands to a let binding the keyform, then nested if/type-predicate tests.
  1650
  1651   FR-001: Evaluates keyform once and dispatches based on type
  1652   FR-002: Expands to nested if forms with predicate tests
  1653   FR-003: Supports multiple type specifiers per clause ((type1 type2) body)
  1654   FR-004: Supports otherwise and t as catch-all clause keys
  1655   FR-005: Returns NIL when no clause matches and no otherwise exists
  1656   FR-006: Evaluates the keyform exactly once, binding to a gensym"
  1657  (lambda (form)
  1658    (let ((keyform (second form))
  1659          (clauses (cddr form))
  1660          (key-var (gensym "KEY-")))
  1661      (labels ((otherwise-clause-p (clause)
  1662                 (let ((type-spec (first clause)))
  1663                   (or (eq type-spec 'otherwise)
  1664                       (eq type-spec 't))))
  1665               (make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1666                 ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1667                 (cond
  1668                   ;; List of multiple types
  1669                   ((and (listp type-spec)
  1670                         (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1671                    (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1672                        (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1673                        (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1674                                            (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1675                                          type-spec))))
  1676                   ;; Single type specifier
  1677                   (t
  1678                    (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1679               (expand-clauses (clauses)
  1680                 (if (null clauses)
  1681                     nil  ; FR-005: Return NIL when no match
  1682                     (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1683                            (type-spec (first clause))
  1684                            (body (rest clause)))
  1685                       (if (otherwise-clause-p clause)
  1686                           ;; FR-004: Otherwise/t clause - just execute body
  1687                           (cons 'progn body)
  1688                           ;; Normal clause - test and branch
  1689                           (list 'if
  1690                                 (make-type-test key-var type-spec)
  1691                                 (cons 'progn body)
  1692                                 (expand-clauses (rest clauses))))))))
  1693        ;; FR-006: Bind keyform to gensym for single evaluation
  1694        (list 'let (list (list key-var keyform))
  1695              (expand-clauses clauses))))))
  1696

  1701(defun make-etypecase-expander ()
  1702  "Create a macro expander for ETYPECASE.
  1703   (etypecase keyform (type form...) ...)
  1704   Like typecase but signals type-error when no clause matches.
  1705   Does NOT allow otherwise/t clauses.
  1706
  1707   FR-007: Evaluates keyform once and dispatches based on type
  1708   FR-008: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type when no match
  1709   FR-009: otherwise/t clauses are NOT allowed
  1710   FR-010: :expected-type is (or type1 type2 ...) of all clause types"
  1711  (lambda (form)
  1712    (let ((keyform (second form))
  1713          (clauses (cddr form))
  1714          (key-var (gensym "KEY-")))
  1715      ;; FR-009: Validate no otherwise/t clauses
  1716      (validate-exhaustive-clauses clauses 'etypecase)
  1717      (let ((expected-type (construct-expected-type clauses)))
  1718        (labels ((make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1719                   ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1720                   (cond
  1721                     ;; List of multiple types
  1722                     ((and (listp type-spec)
  1723                           (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1724                      (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1725                          (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1726                          (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1727                                              (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1728                                            type-spec))))
  1729                     ;; Single type specifier
  1730                     (t
  1731                      (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1732                 (expand-clauses (clauses)
  1733                   (if (null clauses)
  1734                       ;; FR-008: No match - signal type-error
  1735                       (list 'error 'type-error
  1736                             :datum key-var
  1737                             :expected-type (list 'quote expected-type))
  1738                       (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1739                              (type-spec (first clause))
  1740                              (body (rest clause)))
  1741                         ;; Normal clause - test and branch
  1742                         (list 'if
  1743                               (make-type-test key-var type-spec)
  1744                               (cons 'progn body)
  1745                               (expand-clauses (rest clauses)))))))
  1746          ;; Bind keyform to gensym for single evaluation
  1747          (list 'let (list (list key-var keyform))
  1748                (expand-clauses clauses)))))))

  1754(defun make-check-type-expander ()
  1755  "Create a macro expander for CHECK-TYPE.
  1756   (check-type place typespec [type-string])
  1757   Signals type-error with store-value restart if type doesn't match.
  1758   Loops until type matches (after store-value restart).
  1759
  1760   FR-015: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type if place is not of typespec
  1761   FR-016: Returns NIL if type already matches
  1762   FR-017: Provides store-value restart to set a new value
  1763   FR-018: Re-validates after store-value restart (loop until correct)
  1764   FR-019: Optional type-string included in error message"
  1765  (lambda (form)
  1766    (let* ((place (second form))
  1767           (typespec (third form))
  1768           (type-string (fourth form))
  1769           (value-var (gensym "VALUE-")))
  1770      ;; Build the type test predicate using place directly
  1771      (let ((type-test (type-specifier-to-predicate typespec place)))
  1772        ;; FR-018: Loop until type matches
  1773        `(loop
  1774           ;; Check if type matches
  1775           (when ,(if (eq type-test t)
  1776                      t
  1777                      type-test)
  1778             (return nil))  ; FR-016: Return NIL if correct
  1779           ;; FR-015, FR-017: Signal error with store-value restart
  1780           (restart-case
  1781               (error 'type-error
  1782                      :datum ,place
  1783                      :expected-type ',typespec
  1784                      ,@(when type-string
  1785                          (list :format-control type-string)))
  1786             (store-value (,value-var)
  1787               :report "Supply a new value."
  1788               :interactive (lambda () (list (read)))
  1789               ;; Update the place
  1790               (setf ,place ,value-var))))))))
  1791

  1796(defun make-ctypecase-expander ()
  1797  "Create a macro expander for CTYPECASE.
  1798   (ctypecase keyplace (type form...) ...)
  1799   Like etypecase but provides store-value restart for correction.
  1800   Loops until a type matches after store-value.
  1801   Does NOT allow otherwise/t clauses.
  1802
  1803   FR-011: Evaluates place value once per iteration and dispatches based on type
  1804   FR-012: Signals type-error with :datum and :expected-type when no match
  1805   FR-013: Provides store-value restart to set a new value and re-dispatch
  1806   FR-014: otherwise/t clauses are NOT allowed"
  1807  (lambda (form)
  1808    (let ((keyplace (second form))
  1809          (clauses (cddr form))
  1810          (value-var (gensym "VALUE-")))
  1811      ;; FR-014: Validate no otherwise/t clauses
  1812      (validate-exhaustive-clauses clauses 'ctypecase)
  1813      (let ((expected-type (construct-expected-type clauses)))
  1814        (labels ((make-type-test (key-var type-spec)
  1815                   ;; Handle multiple type specifiers: ((type1 type2) body)
  1816                   (cond
  1817                     ;; List of multiple types
  1818                     ((and (listp type-spec)
  1819                           (not (member (car type-spec) '(or and not member satisfies eql))))
  1820                      (if (= 1 (length type-spec))
  1821                          (type-specifier-to-predicate (first type-spec) key-var)
  1822                          (cons 'or (mapcar (lambda (ts)
  1823                                              (type-specifier-to-predicate ts key-var))
  1824                                            type-spec))))
  1825                     ;; Single type specifier
  1826                     (t
  1827                      (type-specifier-to-predicate type-spec key-var))))
  1828                 (expand-clauses-with-return (clauses)
  1829                   ;; Build nested if with returns on match
  1830                   (if (null clauses)
  1831                       nil
  1832                       (let* ((clause (first clauses))
  1833                              (type-spec (first clause))
  1834                              (body (rest clause)))
  1835                         (list 'if
  1836                               (make-type-test keyplace type-spec)
  1837                               (list 'return (cons 'progn body))
  1838                               (expand-clauses-with-return (rest clauses)))))))
  1839          ;; Loop until type matches
  1840          `(loop
  1841             ;; Try to match a clause - return if matched
  1842             ,(expand-clauses-with-return clauses)
  1843             ;; FR-012, FR-013: No match - signal error with store-value restart
  1844             (restart-case
  1845                 (error 'type-error
  1846                        :datum ,keyplace
  1847                        :expected-type ',expected-type)
  1848               (store-value (,value-var)
  1849                 :report "Supply a new value."
  1850                 :interactive (lambda () (list (read)))
  1851                 ;; Update the place and loop to re-dispatch
  1852                 (setf ,keyplace ,value-var)))))))))

  1875(defun make-destructuring-bind-expander ()
  1876  "Create a macro expander for DESTRUCTURING-BIND.
  1877   (destructuring-bind lambda-list expression declaration* form*)
  1878   Binds the variables specified in lambda-list to the corresponding values
  1879   in the list resulting from the evaluation of expression.
  1880
  1881   FR-001: Expands to code that binds variables according to lambda-list pattern
  1882   FR-002: Supports required parameters in flat and nested patterns
  1883   FR-003: Supports &optional parameters with default values and supplied-p
  1884   FR-004: Supports &rest to capture remaining list elements
  1885   FR-005: Supports &key parameters with defaults, supplied-p, and alternate names
  1886   FR-006: Supports &body as a synonym for &rest
  1887   FR-007: Supports &whole to bind entire list before destructuring
  1888   FR-008: Supports &allow-other-keys to permit unrecognized keywords
  1889   FR-009: Signals program-error when required parameters cannot be satisfied
  1890   FR-010: Signals error when excess elements exist and no &rest/&body
  1891   FR-011: Signals error when unrecognized keywords present without &allow-other-keys
  1892   FR-012: Supports nested destructuring patterns at any depth
  1893   FR-013: Handles dotted-list patterns
  1894   FR-014: Evaluates default value forms only when parameter not supplied"
  1895  (lambda (form)
  1896    (let ((lambda-list (second form))
  1897          (expression (third form))
  1898          (body (cdddr form))
  1899          (list-var (gensym "LIST-")))
  1900      ;; Parse the lambda-list
  1901      (let ((parsed-ll (clysm/lib/destructuring:parse-destructuring-lambda-list lambda-list)))
  1902        ;; Generate the binding code
  1903        (list 'let (list (list list-var expression))
  1904              (clysm/lib/destructuring:generate-destructuring-code
  1905               parsed-ll list-var body))))))
